Ahead of the 2023 presidential election, some youths under the auspices of the Wike Volunteer Network have registered their support for the Governor of Rivers State, Nyesom Wike to contest the highest political office in Nigeria. The youths drawn from the South-South, South-East, South-West, and North-East in a statement signed by the Coordinator-General, Comrade Solomon Okoduwa stated that they are planning a massive solidarity rally in the first week of May in Abuja. This, according to Okoduwa, is to woo other regions, to support the nomination of the most competent and courageous Man for the job. He said “the Rivers State Governor has a proven record of excellence, he is a better aspirant and all Nigerians should support him. “We are Nigerian youths, we know what is good for us. Everyone can see his track record in Rivers State. This man is experienced for the top job and can take us out of this wilderness to the promised land.” “Governor Wike will unify, restore hope and confidence in our country. With the creativity, capacity and experience of this man, he will improve the economy of Nigeria to a centre of attraction and creative hub.” “Our movement is a voluntary one for the forthcoming presidential election to rekindle a ray of hope to Nigerians who believe in the personality of His Excellency, Nyesom Wike. “Our movement will use the digital platform, PVC holding members to drive a robust political campaign to support the candidacy of Nyesom Wike for the position of President come 2023. POLL “Transformation Agenda For Nigerians Movement will bring together every Nigerian in respective tribe and ethnicity for the realization of this noble goal. “We will be in touch with volunteers from all walks of life for this assignment to usher His Excellency, Ezenwo Nyesom Wike in 2023,” Okoduwa added.